[knock at door]

1244
01:03:28,083 --> 01:03:29,083
Mm…

1245
01:03:34,375 --> 01:03:36,083
Oh, Poppy.

1246
01:03:37,167 --> 01:03:38,417
I think I'm dreaming.

1247
01:03:38,500 --> 01:03:41,083
You're not dreaming,
but you are burning up.

1248
01:03:41,167 --> 01:03:43,333
Mm, but you're in Norway.

1249
01:03:43,417 --> 01:03:44,417
Obviously not.

1250
01:03:45,667 --> 01:03:49,000
Okay, let's get you back in bed.
See if we can get rid of this fever.

1251
01:03:49,083 --> 01:03:51,958
But how are you supposed...
You're gonna be late for your flight.

1252
01:03:52,042 --> 01:03:54,542
I already missed my flight two hours ago.
Come on.

1253
01:03:54,625 --> 01:03:56,833
But you're supposed to be in Norway.

1254
01:03:56,917 --> 01:03:59,708
What's the point of being in Norway
if you're not there?

1255
01:03:59,792 --> 01:04:03,083
I was gonna take you
to a freaking hotel made of ice.

1256
01:04:03,167 --> 01:04:04,167
[Alex chuckles]

1257
01:04:04,583 --> 01:04:07,750
Well, how about later on
we can stick our heads in the freezer

1258
01:04:07,833 --> 01:04:09,417
and pretend we're there, okay?

1259
01:04:09,500 --> 01:04:10,500
- No.
- Come on.

1260
01:04:10,542 --> 01:04:11,542
Lay down.

1261
01:04:12,667 --> 01:04:13,667
Okay.

1262
01:04:19,458 --> 01:04:21,458
[pleasant music plays]

1263
01:04:22,375 --> 01:04:23,375
[Alex chuckles]

1264
01:04:28,458 --> 01:04:30,500
Mm, I'm gonna get you sick.

1265
01:04:31,417 --> 01:04:33,375
I have the whole week off anyway.

1266
01:04:36,125 --> 01:04:37,667
Do your worst.

1267
01:04:45,042 --> 01:04:47,208
I do not deserve you.

1268
01:04:48,250 --> 01:04:49,250
I know.

1269
01:04:49,917 --> 01:04:50,750
[snickers]

1270
01:04:50,833 --> 01:04:52,375
[snickers]

1271
01:04:54,583 --> 01:04:56,208
Chicken noodle soup?

1272
01:04:56,792 --> 01:04:58,333
[quietly] Chicken noodle soup.

1273
01:05:06,292 --> 01:05:07,292
[sighs]

1274
01:05:07,917 --> 01:05:09,917
[pleasant music continues]

1275
01:05:14,292 --> 01:05:15,792
[exhales]

1276
01:05:18,292 --> 01:05:19,292
Mm…

1277
01:05:40,833 --> 01:05:41,833
[sighs]

1278
01:05:42,542 --> 01:05:44,125
[dishes clatter]

1279
01:05:49,208 --> 01:05:50,458
You went running?

1280
01:05:50,542 --> 01:05:52,125
You madman.

1281
01:05:55,208 --> 01:05:56,250
Are you ignoring me?

1282
01:05:58,792 --> 01:05:59,792
Oh. [Chuckles]

1283
01:06:00,708 --> 01:06:01,708
Alex.

1284
01:06:02,208 --> 01:06:03,792
Hello. Alex!

1285
01:06:04,667 --> 01:06:07,667
Wow. Alex. Hello? Alex!

1286
01:06:07,750 --> 01:06:09,333
- [Alex shouts]
- Sorry! [Laughs]

1287
01:06:09,833 --> 01:06:11,833
Shit, sorry. You scared me.

1288
01:06:11,917 --> 01:06:15,917
- Those are very noise-canceling.
- Oh, yeah. [Pants]

1289
01:06:17,208 --> 01:06:18,583
- Morning.
- Good morning.

1290
01:06:18,667 --> 01:06:19,792
How'd you sleep?

1291
01:06:20,500 --> 01:06:21,792
Oh, it was very cozy.

1292
01:06:22,417 --> 01:06:24,708
I felt like I was being cremated.

1293
01:06:24,792 --> 01:06:26,125
Yeah, me too.

1294
01:06:27,000 --> 01:06:29,125
You went running? What about your back?

1295
01:06:29,208 --> 01:06:31,500
Oh, no, it's good. It loosens me up.

1296
01:06:31,583 --> 01:06:32,750
That's what you think,

1297
01:06:32,833 --> 01:06:35,667
but I've never run once,
and my back is great.

1298
01:06:36,292 --> 01:06:38,250
I'm sorry, you've never run once?

1299
01:06:38,333 --> 01:06:40,000
I almost failed PE.

1300
01:06:40,083 --> 01:06:40,958
On principle.

1301
01:06:41,042 --> 01:06:42,042
[Alex scoffs]

1302
01:06:43,375 --> 01:06:44,917
Here. Made coffee.

1303
01:06:45,792 --> 01:06:46,917
Well, thank you.

1304
01:06:52,667 --> 01:06:55,000
Listen, I don't know
what your plans are today, but…

1305
01:06:55,958 --> 01:06:58,208
You wanna come
to the rehearsal dinner tonight?

1306
01:06:58,292 --> 01:06:59,667
Oh. Uh…

1307
01:07:01,042 --> 01:07:02,500
I mean, am I invited?

1308
01:07:03,208 --> 01:07:06,417
Isn't it kind of just for family
and the wedding party?

1309
01:07:06,500 --> 01:07:07,792
Yeah, but…

1310
01:07:08,625 --> 01:07:10,958
I mean, you're basically family, Poppy.

1311
01:07:11,875 --> 01:07:14,833
And I think David
would really like it if you came.

1312
01:07:16,083 --> 01:07:17,083
Okay.

1313
01:07:17,583 --> 01:07:18,583
Okay.

1314
01:07:20,542 --> 01:07:22,542
["August" by Taylor Swift plays]

1315
01:07:25,875 --> 01:07:28,000
<i>♪ Salt air ♪</i>

1316
01:07:28,875 --> 01:07:31,542
<i>♪ And the rust on your door ♪</i>

1317
01:07:31,625 --> 01:07:36,417
<i>♪ I never needed anything more ♪</i>

1318
01:07:36,500 --> 01:07:39,250
<i>♪ Whispers ♪</i>

1319
01:07:39,333 --> 01:07:41,875
<i>♪ Of, "Are you sure?" ♪</i>

1320
01:07:42,375 --> 01:07:46,167
<i>♪ "Never have I ever before" ♪</i>

1321
01:07:46,250 --> 01:07:49,250
<i>♪ But I can see us lost in the memory ♪</i>

1322
01:07:49,333 --> 01:07:52,708
<i>♪ August slipped away
Into a moment in time ♪</i>

1323
01:07:53,208 --> 01:07:55,917
<i>♪ 'Cause it was never mine ♪</i>

1324
01:07:57,333 --> 01:07:59,875
<i>♪ And I can see us twisted in bedsheets ♪</i>

1325
01:07:59,958 --> 01:08:03,667
<i>♪ August slipped away
Like a bottle of wine… ♪</i>

1326
01:08:04,667 --> 01:08:06,250
- Hi.
- Hey.

1327
01:08:07,792 --> 01:08:10,292
Since when are you so fashionably on time?

1328
01:08:10,375 --> 01:08:13,167
Since when are you
so fashionably fashionable?

1329
01:08:15,292 --> 01:08:16,625
You look beautiful.

1330
01:08:18,417 --> 01:08:19,417
Thank you.

1331
01:08:21,333 --> 01:08:23,750
- Is that Miss Poppy Wright?
- [Poppy gasps]

1332
01:08:24,667 --> 01:08:26,875
Bring it in, Mr. Nilsen. Oh my gosh!

1333
01:08:26,958 --> 01:08:28,333
I missed you!

1334
01:08:29,417 --> 01:08:30,792
Hey, congratulations.

1335
01:08:30,875 --> 01:08:32,167
Oh, thank you.

1336
01:08:32,875 --> 01:08:35,042
How come I never see you in Linfield?

1337
01:08:35,125 --> 01:08:38,042
Oh, uh, because she wouldn't
be caught dead there, Dad.

1338
01:08:38,125 --> 01:08:41,083
Oh, your son is a liar and a coward.
I love Linfield.

1339
01:08:41,167 --> 01:08:44,917
In fact, I think that we should get
matching Linfield tattoos. You in, Ed?

1340
01:08:45,875 --> 01:08:48,250
- [David] What's going on over here?
- David!

1341
01:08:49,667 --> 01:08:50,750
Oh my God!

1342
01:08:50,833 --> 01:08:53,042
Your dad and I are getting
matching tramp stamps.

1343
01:08:53,125 --> 01:08:56,500
- Alex is still undecided.
- This is why I wanted you here.

1344
01:08:56,583 --> 01:08:58,792
You look, like… amazing.

1345
01:08:58,875 --> 01:09:00,833
Wait, now you have to meet…

1346
01:09:00,917 --> 01:09:02,792
Nam, hi!

1347
01:09:02,875 --> 01:09:03,875
Finally!

1348
01:09:03,917 --> 01:09:05,917
No, you're right. [Laughs] You're right.

1349
01:09:06,000 --> 01:09:08,333
Alex would never.
He'd never go skinny-dipping.

1350
01:09:08,917 --> 01:09:12,458
- But Vacation Alex…
- [Nam] Mm?

1351
01:09:12,542 --> 01:09:13,792
[David] Okay, just to be clear,

1352
01:09:13,875 --> 01:09:16,542
the wedding tomorrow
is not clothing optional.

1353
01:09:16,625 --> 01:09:18,083
Please, please respect this.

1354
01:09:18,167 --> 01:09:20,417
Okay, let's not say things
we can't take back.

1355
01:09:21,292 --> 01:09:22,167
Thank you.

1356
01:09:22,250 --> 01:09:25,833
I don't think I've ever met
this Vacation Alex.

1357
01:09:25,917 --> 01:09:27,792
Ooh, you're missing out. He's fun.

1358
01:09:27,875 --> 01:09:31,750
You know, one time
I caught him trying on my romper.

1359
01:09:31,833 --> 01:09:34,667
- [Nam gasps]
- Okay, that is very out of context.

1360
01:09:34,750 --> 01:09:36,458
Do you want me to give some context?

1361
01:09:36,542 --> 01:09:37,958
[Nam] Photos or it didn't happen.

1362
01:09:38,042 --> 01:09:40,792
I'm so glad you got out
of your work thing.

1363
01:09:40,875 --> 01:09:42,208
You can go to Greece anytime.

1364
01:09:42,292 --> 01:09:44,532
- ["August" continues in background]
- [inaudible dialogue]

1365
01:09:56,750 --> 01:09:58,708
[thunder rumbles in the distance]

1366
01:09:59,208 --> 01:10:00,833
Thanks for walking me home.

1367
01:10:01,417 --> 01:10:02,417
[Poppy chuckles]

1368
01:10:03,000 --> 01:10:04,000
[Alex snickers]

1369
01:10:06,125 --> 01:10:07,875
Yeah, well, I guess I'll see you tomorrow.

1370
01:10:09,542 --> 01:10:10,917
Why did you come here?

1371
01:10:12,042 --> 01:10:13,208
What do you mean?

1372
01:10:13,292 --> 01:10:17,833
What I mean is, you told me that <i>R&R</i>
was sending you to Barcelona anyway.

1373
01:10:19,125 --> 01:10:21,000
But that wasn't true, was it?

1374
01:10:24,750 --> 01:10:26,458
I miss my best friend.

1375
01:10:28,375 --> 01:10:29,542
I missed you too.

1376
01:10:30,125 --> 01:10:32,125
[gentle music plays]

1377
01:10:34,042 --> 01:10:35,417
I just wish that…

1378
01:10:36,833 --> 01:10:39,542
We could go back
to the way things were before Tuscany.

1379
01:10:44,917 --> 01:10:47,125
I don't think that's possible.

1380
01:10:57,917 --> 01:10:59,500
I'll see you tomorrow.

1381
01:11:03,625 --> 01:11:04,625
[mumbles]

1382
01:11:05,417 --> 01:11:06,417
[sighs]

1383
01:11:13,083 --> 01:11:15,583
["L-O-V-E (Italian Version)"
by Nat King Cole plays]

1384
01:11:51,750 --> 01:11:52,833
Wow.

1385
01:11:52,917 --> 01:11:54,042
- This is…
- [Sarah gasps]

1386
01:11:54,708 --> 01:11:55,542
…huge.

1387
01:11:55,625 --> 01:11:56,625
Wow.

1388
01:11:57,042 --> 01:11:58,042
[door opens]

1389
01:11:58,125 --> 01:11:59,500
Hi!

1390
01:11:59,583 --> 01:12:01,250
- There she is.
- [Poppy] You made it!

1391
01:12:01,333 --> 01:12:03,292
- Yes!
- Uh, Poppy, this is Sarah.

1392
01:12:03,375 --> 01:12:04,708
- Sarah, this is Poppy.
- Hi.

1393
01:12:04,792 --> 01:12:06,000
- [Sarah] Hello. Hi.
- Hey.

1394
01:12:06,083 --> 01:12:08,208
- Oh my gosh, this is...
- Oh! So weird.

1395
01:12:08,292 --> 01:12:10,792
- I feel like I already know you.
- [Sarah] Yeah, same.

1396
01:12:11,625 --> 01:12:14,417
I can't believe I finally
get to meet the famous Poppy.

1397
01:12:17,083 --> 01:12:18,875
This place is stunning.

1398
01:12:18,958 --> 01:12:21,750
- Thank you so much for letting us come.
- Oh, no.

1399
01:12:21,833 --> 01:12:24,250
Thank <i>R&R.</i>
I have done nothing to deserve this.

1400
01:12:24,333 --> 01:12:26,000
- Hi! Hey.
- [man] <i>Benvenuto.</i>

1401
01:12:26,583 --> 01:12:27,708
This is Trey.

1402
01:12:28,292 --> 01:12:29,792
- Hi, Trey.
- Hey, Trey.

1403
01:12:29,875 --> 01:12:31,458
I've heard great things.

1404
01:12:31,542 --> 01:12:34,333
He's being nice.
I've done nothing but complain about you.

1405
01:12:35,625 --> 01:12:37,208
Come on. Come see.

1406
01:12:37,708 --> 01:12:39,833
It's actually pretty amazing inside.

1407
01:12:39,917 --> 01:12:41,292
- Stop!
- ["L-O-V-E" ends]

1408
01:12:41,375 --> 01:12:43,542
- [Poppy] Cheers!
- [Sarah] Cheers!

1409
01:12:46,000 --> 01:12:47,250
- [Alex] Mm.
- [Poppy] Mm-hm.

1410
01:12:47,333 --> 01:12:48,375
That's good.

1411
01:12:50,958 --> 01:12:52,333
It's a gorgeous spread.

1412
01:12:53,250 --> 01:12:55,333
There's eight different types of cheeses.

1413
01:12:55,417 --> 01:12:57,292
- Oh. Nice.
- Oh, wow. Cool.

1414
01:12:57,375 --> 01:12:59,583
So if you try them all,
we'll do a ranking.

1415
01:13:00,417 --> 01:13:01,417
Ranking?

1416
01:13:02,250 --> 01:13:04,083
- I went a little overboard.
- [Alex] No.

1417
01:13:04,167 --> 01:13:06,625
I'm just so excited
that we're all here together,

1418
01:13:06,708 --> 01:13:09,750
and I think that, you know,
we've taken way too long to do this.

1419
01:13:09,833 --> 01:13:13,708
It's gonna be jarring with you here.
Who is Alex gonna be texting nonstop?

1420
01:13:15,083 --> 01:13:18,292
Is that wine okay? I have a Chablis.
It's the one in Napa you liked.

1421
01:13:18,375 --> 01:13:19,542
Ooh, that was good.

1422
01:13:19,625 --> 01:13:21,625
Oh, uh, no, this is great.

1423
01:13:21,708 --> 01:13:22,708
Okay.

1424
01:13:28,500 --> 01:13:30,083
[jazzy piano music plays]

1425
01:13:32,833 --> 01:13:35,167
I was a professional surfer
for a bunch of years.

1426
01:13:35,250 --> 01:13:38,792
Then my photos
started getting published a lot.

1427
01:13:38,875 --> 01:13:39,750
[Poppy] Mm…

1428
01:13:39,833 --> 01:13:41,625
Started freelancing for <i>R&R.</i>

1429
01:13:42,208 --> 01:13:44,417
Now I get to travel the world
with my girlfriend.

1430
01:13:44,500 --> 01:13:45,958
Have someone else foot the bill.

1431
01:13:46,042 --> 01:13:47,375
That's not bad.

1432
01:13:47,458 --> 01:13:49,375
God, I never heard of jobs like this.

1433
01:13:49,458 --> 01:13:51,958
I wanna sue my high school
guidance counselor.

1434
01:13:52,042 --> 01:13:54,958
No, you have a great job too.
You work with your family, right?

1435
01:13:55,042 --> 01:13:57,958
Yeah, I don't wanna bore you.
It's not as cool as you guys.

1436
01:13:58,042 --> 01:14:01,750
I think me and Poppy would crawl out
of our skin if we were stuck in one place.

1437
01:14:01,833 --> 01:14:04,000
Mortgage. Mailbox.

1438
01:14:04,083 --> 01:14:05,625
You don't have a mailbox?

1439
01:14:05,708 --> 01:14:07,417
We have wanderlust.

1440
01:14:08,542 --> 01:14:10,667
- That's why we're good together.
- Oh.

1441
01:14:11,292 --> 01:14:13,417
We're nomads, mate.

1442
01:14:15,458 --> 01:14:16,458
Aren't we?

1443
01:14:17,458 --> 01:14:19,042
[Poppy] Mm-hm. Mm…

1444
01:14:24,667 --> 01:14:25,667
Okay.

1445
01:14:26,458 --> 01:14:28,250
I'm gonna clear the table now.

1446
01:14:28,750 --> 01:14:32,083
- I'm being a great hostess.
- [Trey] Mm.

1447
01:14:32,167 --> 01:14:33,917
Living like that would drive me crazy.

1448
01:14:34,500 --> 01:14:35,500
What?

1449
01:14:36,625 --> 01:14:38,250
You love seeing new places.

1450
01:14:38,333 --> 01:14:39,333
Yeah.

1451
01:14:39,708 --> 01:14:42,292
But I like coming home from them too.

1452
01:14:43,542 --> 01:14:46,167
That's what makes
these trips special, right?

1453
01:14:46,250 --> 01:14:47,750
You get to come home.

1454
01:14:49,083 --> 01:14:50,583
What's wrong with home?

1455
01:14:51,792 --> 01:14:53,250
I couldn't agree more.

1456
01:14:53,333 --> 01:14:54,708
Would you pass me that?

1457
01:15:04,375 --> 01:15:06,375
[chill pop plays in background]

1458
01:15:15,250 --> 01:15:19,625
Your mate Alex,
he's a bit of a wet lettuce, isn't he?

1459
01:15:21,333 --> 01:15:23,292
I'm joking. Come on.

1460
01:15:25,708 --> 01:15:27,958
- Are you all right?
- I think I need to get out.

1461
01:15:28,542 --> 01:15:30,708
Hey, you just got in.

1462
01:15:32,375 --> 01:15:35,167
I don't feel good.
I think I'm gonna call it a night.

1463
01:15:35,917 --> 01:15:36,958
Okay.

1464
01:15:40,500 --> 01:15:41,500
Uh…

1465
01:15:42,417 --> 01:15:43,417
Uh…

1466
01:15:44,875 --> 01:15:45,875
[sighs]

1467
01:15:46,750 --> 01:15:47,750
Uh…

1468
01:15:49,083 --> 01:15:50,083
[sighs]

1469
01:15:56,333 --> 01:15:58,292
[tapping keyboard]

1470
01:16:01,917 --> 01:16:04,917
[quietly] Shit. Shit.

1471
01:16:07,792 --> 01:16:09,333
They are not gonna last.

1472
01:16:11,208 --> 01:16:12,208
[Sarah] What do you mean?

1473
01:16:13,333 --> 01:16:14,583
They're nomads.

1474
01:16:14,667 --> 01:16:17,875
- [both laugh]
- [phone buzzes]

1475
01:16:20,500 --> 01:16:21,500
[phone buzzes]

1476
01:16:24,708 --> 01:16:25,958
Let me guess.

1477
01:16:26,042 --> 01:16:28,375
Yeah, she's fully freaking out.

1478
01:16:28,458 --> 01:16:29,500
[phone buzzes]

1479
01:16:29,583 --> 01:16:30,583
Jeez.

1480
01:16:32,375 --> 01:16:35,208
I should probably go check on her, right?

1481
01:16:36,917 --> 01:16:39,417
Yeah, that's fine. Of course.
Go check on your friend.

1482
01:16:39,500 --> 01:16:40,708
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

1483
01:16:40,792 --> 01:16:42,042
I'm gonna go to bed.

1484
01:16:42,125 --> 01:16:43,167
- Okay.
- Yeah.

1485
01:16:43,250 --> 01:16:45,250
- Okay. I love you.
- Kiss. Love you.

1486
01:16:46,250 --> 01:16:47,250
- Okay.
- Bye.

1487
01:16:53,625 --> 01:16:54,833
[door opens]

1488
01:16:56,208 --> 01:16:58,000
- [whispers] I'm sorry.
- Hey, it's okay.

1489
01:16:58,083 --> 01:16:59,917
- I'm sorry.
- What is it? What's wrong?

1490
01:17:00,000 --> 01:17:01,708
I think I'm pregnant.

1491
01:17:03,917 --> 01:17:05,542
That is so bad.

1492
01:17:06,125 --> 01:17:07,458
I don't know what to do.

1493
01:17:07,542 --> 01:17:09,500
Well, why isn't Trey here?

1494
01:17:11,917 --> 01:17:13,542
I didn't tell him.

1495
01:17:17,708 --> 01:17:18,708
Oh.

1496
01:17:20,958 --> 01:17:21,958
Oh…

1497
01:17:22,708 --> 01:17:24,333
We should get you a test.

1498
01:17:25,250 --> 01:17:27,000
[phone app chimes]

1499
01:17:55,417 --> 01:17:56,500
It's negative.

1500
01:18:09,125 --> 01:18:10,625
[gentle music plays]

1501
01:18:11,333 --> 01:18:14,125
Hey. Hey.

1502
01:18:16,958 --> 01:18:18,917
That's a… that's a good thing, right?

1503
01:18:22,917 --> 01:18:24,750
No, I'm relieved. I'm just…

1504
01:18:26,667 --> 01:18:27,500
Scared.

1505
01:18:27,583 --> 01:18:29,208
Yeah. It's okay.

1506
01:18:30,875 --> 01:18:31,958
It's okay.

1507
01:18:34,500 --> 01:18:35,958
Hey, breathe, okay?

1508
01:18:38,667 --> 01:18:40,000
Just breathe.

1509
01:18:41,667 --> 01:18:42,875
I'm here.

1510
01:18:43,875 --> 01:18:45,500
For you. I'm here, okay?

1511
01:18:46,833 --> 01:18:48,083
I'll always be here.

1512
01:18:51,500 --> 01:18:52,500
[Poppy sniffs]

1513
01:19:23,250 --> 01:19:24,250
[whispers] Wait.

1514
01:19:24,792 --> 01:19:26,000
I'm sorry.

1515
01:19:29,542 --> 01:19:31,458
- I'm sorry.
- Whoa…

1516
01:19:32,042 --> 01:19:33,042
I'm sorry.

1517
01:19:36,042 --> 01:19:37,250
What was that?

1518
01:19:37,333 --> 01:19:38,417
I didn't mean it.

1519
01:19:40,500 --> 01:19:42,375
No, I'm just confused, and I'm…

1520
01:19:44,500 --> 01:19:45,667
All turned around.

1521
01:19:45,750 --> 01:19:47,083
But I didn't mean it.

1522
01:19:47,667 --> 01:19:48,667
I…

1523
01:19:51,250 --> 01:19:52,333
What am I to you?

1524
01:19:54,625 --> 01:19:55,750
You're my friend.

1525
01:19:57,042 --> 01:19:58,042
[Alex sighs]

1526
01:19:59,000 --> 01:20:00,125
My best friend.

1527
01:20:01,583 --> 01:20:02,583
[Alex exhales]

1528
01:20:03,708 --> 01:20:05,250
I don't wanna ruin that.

1529
01:20:10,667 --> 01:20:11,667
I'm sorry.

1530
01:20:18,417 --> 01:20:19,417
No.

1531
01:20:19,958 --> 01:20:20,958
It's fine.

1532
01:20:26,417 --> 01:20:27,417
[door opens]

1533
01:20:29,000 --> 01:20:30,000
[Poppy] Mm…

1534
01:20:30,917 --> 01:20:31,917
[Trey] Woohoo!

1535
01:20:32,417 --> 01:20:33,792
Get out here!

1536
01:20:33,875 --> 01:20:34,958
What?

1537
01:20:35,042 --> 01:20:36,917
[Trey] Come on out here!
Get your ass out here!

1538
01:20:37,000 --> 01:20:39,000
- All right.
- [Trey] This is crazy!

1539
01:20:39,583 --> 01:20:42,625
[laughs] Hold it.
Babe, you gotta see this.

1540
01:20:42,708 --> 01:20:43,833
Come on!

1541
01:20:43,917 --> 01:20:45,708
- What?
- Look!

1542
01:20:45,792 --> 01:20:46,917
Jeez.

1543
01:20:47,500 --> 01:20:48,958
I said yes!

1544
01:20:50,250 --> 01:20:51,250
[Trey] This is crazy.

1545
01:20:51,292 --> 01:20:54,000
He asked me at the most
beautiful spot on our walk.

1546
01:20:54,083 --> 01:20:55,458
He's such a romantic.

1547
01:20:56,042 --> 01:20:57,917
Oh my God! Oh my God!

1548
01:20:58,000 --> 01:21:00,875
Congratulations, you guys! What?

1549
01:21:00,958 --> 01:21:02,917
Thank you! I'm so happy!

1550
01:21:03,000 --> 01:21:04,542
- Thanks. Thank you.
- [Trey] Hold on.

1551
01:21:04,625 --> 01:21:07,417
You nipped out this morning
and bought a ring?

1552
01:21:07,500 --> 01:21:09,667
No, no, I've had it for a while.

1553
01:21:10,542 --> 01:21:13,750
Just… waiting for the right moment.

1554
01:21:14,417 --> 01:21:16,542
Well, come on, girl. Let me see that ring.

1555
01:21:17,042 --> 01:21:18,042
Come on.

1556
01:21:19,042 --> 01:21:21,000
Oh my God! [Giggles]

1557
01:21:23,750 --> 01:21:25,750
[pensive music plays]

1558
01:21:37,250 --> 01:21:39,250
[pensive music continues]

1559
01:21:43,833 --> 01:21:45,833
[pensive music fades out]

1560
01:21:57,583 --> 01:21:58,750
I'm happy for you.

1561
01:22:00,208 --> 01:22:01,208
I am.

1562
01:22:02,417 --> 01:22:03,542
Thank you.

1563
01:22:04,833 --> 01:22:06,292
Yeah, it was… it was time.

1564
01:22:08,417 --> 01:22:10,208
What's the plan? What are you gonna do?

1565
01:22:11,708 --> 01:22:13,458
We're gonna stay in Linfield.

1566
01:22:16,458 --> 01:22:17,458
[Poppy scoffs]

1567
01:22:18,667 --> 01:22:19,667
What?

1568
01:22:21,375 --> 01:22:23,083
What about your PhD?

1569
01:22:24,417 --> 01:22:27,542
What about teaching in Europe?

1570
01:22:28,708 --> 01:22:30,208
Or New York?

1571
01:22:31,833 --> 01:22:34,125
- You always said that was your dream.
- Yeah.

1572
01:22:34,208 --> 01:22:37,917
- So what are you gonna do in Linfield?
- I'm gonna teach at the high school.

1573
01:22:39,292 --> 01:22:41,750
Sarah's gonna take over
her dad's real estate business.

1574
01:22:41,833 --> 01:22:44,083
What does that have to do
with what you want?

1575
01:22:46,292 --> 01:22:47,292
Well…

1576
01:22:48,000 --> 01:22:53,625
What I want is a stable,
loving relationship.

1577
01:22:55,333 --> 01:22:57,458
And sometimes that takes sacrifice.

1578
01:22:59,042 --> 01:23:00,458
It's called compromise.

1579
01:23:03,375 --> 01:23:07,667
- Alex, I think it's called settling.
- Uh… [scoffs]

1580
01:23:09,125 --> 01:23:10,125
Yeah.

1581
01:23:11,792 --> 01:23:16,667
You would think that
because you live in a fantasy land, Poppy.

1582
01:23:19,000 --> 01:23:21,583
Always running away to new places.

1583
01:23:22,708 --> 01:23:24,375
New friends.

1584
01:23:24,875 --> 01:23:26,083
New connections.

1585
01:23:26,875 --> 01:23:29,583
But Sarah and I,
we're building something together.

1586
01:23:29,667 --> 01:23:30,917
Something real.

1587
01:23:31,000 --> 01:23:32,875
That sounds like what Sarah wants.

1588
01:23:35,375 --> 01:23:36,792
That's what I want.

1589
01:23:48,958 --> 01:23:51,292
I think this is our last trip together.

1590
01:23:53,958 --> 01:23:55,958
[sad music plays]

1591
01:24:16,125 --> 01:24:17,792
[thunder rumbles]

1592
01:24:28,125 --> 01:24:29,125
Hmmm…

1593
01:24:32,667 --> 01:24:34,125
[purse crashes]

1594
01:24:34,625 --> 01:24:36,625
[thunder continues]

1595
01:24:43,750 --> 01:24:45,750
[control beeps]

1596
01:24:47,125 --> 01:24:48,167
[beeping]

1597
01:24:48,250 --> 01:24:49,250
[scoffs]

1598
01:24:50,000 --> 01:24:52,208
[door opens]

1599
01:24:52,792 --> 01:24:53,792
[Poppy grumbles]

1600
01:25:00,167 --> 01:25:03,042
I don't wanna go back
to how things were before Tuscany.

1601
01:25:05,250 --> 01:25:06,667
It doesn't work for me.

1602
01:25:06,750 --> 01:25:08,625
It's too hot in here.

1603
01:25:08,708 --> 01:25:12,375
I can't have this conversation.

1604
01:25:12,458 --> 01:25:15,583
Like, I can't even breathe in here.

1605
01:25:15,667 --> 01:25:16,667
I need…

1606
01:25:17,458 --> 01:25:18,542
Air.

1607
01:25:19,167 --> 01:25:20,458
Did you hear me?

1608
01:25:21,208 --> 01:25:22,208
I heard you.

1609
01:25:23,750 --> 01:25:24,833
[scoffs]

1610
01:25:29,750 --> 01:25:31,583
Why did you and Sarah break up?

1611
01:25:32,625 --> 01:25:33,625
[sighs]

1612
01:25:35,292 --> 01:25:37,083
Why did you and Sarah break up?

1613
01:25:37,667 --> 01:25:40,042
- A lot of reasons.
- That's such bullshit.

1614
01:25:42,208 --> 01:25:45,000
The last time I saw you,
you just got engaged,

1615
01:25:45,083 --> 01:25:48,417
and then you ghosted me for two years.

1616
01:25:49,625 --> 01:25:51,875
And then you broke off the engagement.

1617
01:25:53,667 --> 01:25:57,000
- Now you can't say three words about it.
- What do you want me to tell you?

1618
01:25:59,167 --> 01:26:01,542
I want you to tell me it's not my fault.

1619
01:26:03,792 --> 01:26:06,917
Tell me I'm not the reason
you're not married right now.

1620
01:26:09,000 --> 01:26:12,542
Tell me that… it's not because of me.

1621
01:26:18,667 --> 01:26:20,458
Of course it's because of you.

1622
01:26:24,042 --> 01:26:25,042
Right.

1623
01:26:29,542 --> 01:26:30,708
What are you doing?

1624
01:26:32,292 --> 01:26:33,292
Poppy.

1625
01:26:37,375 --> 01:26:39,792
- Poppy, what are you doing?
- I need air!

1626
01:26:56,708 --> 01:26:57,708
[Alex] Poppy.

1627
01:27:00,417 --> 01:27:01,250
Poppy.

1628
01:27:01,333 --> 01:27:02,667
I messed up, okay?

1629
01:27:04,208 --> 01:27:07,625
Whatever we are, whatever this is,
I asked too much of you.

1630
01:27:09,542 --> 01:27:11,625
Friends shouldn't ask
that much of each other.

1631
01:27:11,708 --> 01:27:14,375
I don't wanna be
your fucking friend, Poppy.

1632
01:27:15,958 --> 01:27:17,083
I want you.

1633
01:27:18,667 --> 01:27:22,250
But you, you don't know what you want.
You never have.

1634
01:27:28,083 --> 01:27:29,208
I want you too.

1635
01:27:29,292 --> 01:27:31,792
- You don't mean that.
- Don't tell me what I mean.

1636
01:27:35,083 --> 01:27:36,667
Why do you think I'm here?

1637
01:27:42,250 --> 01:27:43,375
Because I love you.

1638
01:27:47,583 --> 01:27:48,583
Since when?

1639
01:27:54,583 --> 01:27:55,958
Probably always.

1640
01:27:56,708 --> 01:27:58,708
[serene music plays]

1641
01:28:15,125 --> 01:28:17,125
[serene music turns energetic]

1642
01:29:02,208 --> 01:29:04,208
[serene music continues]

1643
01:29:34,583 --> 01:29:36,583
[serene music continues]

1644
01:29:43,542 --> 01:29:45,875
You skipped your run.

1645
01:29:51,292 --> 01:29:52,750
I didn't wanna leave.

1646
01:29:54,292 --> 01:29:55,667
I never wanna leave.

1647
01:29:58,000 --> 01:29:59,000
So…

1648
01:30:02,375 --> 01:30:04,708
What is on the itinerary today?

1649
01:30:05,417 --> 01:30:06,417
[Alex] Mm…

1650
01:30:07,167 --> 01:30:08,625
I'm thinking we wing it.

1651
01:30:09,292 --> 01:30:10,292
[Poppy] Hm…

1652
01:30:10,792 --> 01:30:14,292
["When I Get My Hands on You"
by The New Basement Tapes plays]

1653
01:30:18,833 --> 01:30:20,167
Can you clip my dress?

1654
01:30:22,667 --> 01:30:23,667
[Alex] Uh…

1655
01:30:27,208 --> 01:30:28,208
No.

1656
01:30:29,208 --> 01:30:31,583
<i>♪ When I set my eyes on you ♪</i>

1657
01:30:35,792 --> 01:30:38,625
<i>♪ Gonna keep you out of town at night ♪</i>

1658
01:30:39,417 --> 01:30:41,417
- [Alex breathes deeply]
- [Poppy groans]

1659
01:30:43,333 --> 01:30:45,708
<i>♪ When I set my eyes on you ♪</i>

1660
01:30:50,042 --> 01:30:53,042
<i>♪ Not gonna be out of my sight ♪</i>

1661
01:30:58,250 --> 01:30:59,875
<i>♪ Now you know ♪</i>

1662
01:31:00,917 --> 01:31:02,792
<i>♪ Everywhere on Earth you go ♪</i>

1663
01:31:02,875 --> 01:31:06,333
<i>♪ You're gonna have me as your man ♪</i>

1664
01:31:17,250 --> 01:31:19,250
["When I Get My Hands on You" continues]

1665
01:31:26,542 --> 01:31:27,625
[song ends]

1666
01:31:27,708 --> 01:31:30,458
[officiant] Do you, Nam and David,

1667
01:31:30,958 --> 01:31:33,875
take each other
to be your wedded husbands?

1668
01:31:34,542 --> 01:31:36,667
- You bet I do.
- I definitely do. Yes.

1669
01:31:37,167 --> 01:31:39,875
[officiant] And now,
by the power vested in me,

1670
01:31:40,375 --> 01:31:43,667
I pronounce you duly married.

1671
01:31:44,167 --> 01:31:45,708
You may kiss your husband.

1672
01:31:45,792 --> 01:31:47,125
[cheers and applause]

1673
01:31:47,208 --> 01:31:49,500
["Stumblin' In" by Cyril plays]

1674
01:31:53,042 --> 01:31:55,250
<i>♪ Our love is alive ♪</i>

1675
01:31:56,792 --> 01:31:58,958
<i>♪ And so we begin ♪</i>

1676
01:32:01,083 --> 01:32:03,250
<i>♪ Foolishly layin' our hearts ♪</i>

1677
01:32:03,333 --> 01:32:04,750
<i>♪ On the table ♪</i>

1678
01:32:04,833 --> 01:32:06,250
<i>♪ Stumblin' in ♪</i>

1679
01:32:08,167 --> 01:32:10,208
<i>♪ Our love is a flame ♪</i>

1680
01:32:12,458 --> 01:32:13,792
<i>♪ Burnin' within ♪</i>

1681
01:32:16,292 --> 01:32:17,333
<i>♪ Now and then ♪</i>

1682
01:32:17,417 --> 01:32:21,708
<i>♪ Firelight will catch us stumblin' in ♪</i>

1683
01:32:23,667 --> 01:32:25,792
<i>♪ Wherever you go… ♪</i>

1684
01:32:26,417 --> 01:32:27,833
That's a heck of a girl.

1685
01:32:27,917 --> 01:32:28,917
<i>♪ Whatever you do… ♪</i>

1686
01:32:29,875 --> 01:32:30,875
[Alex] Yeah.

1687
01:32:31,500 --> 01:32:37,292
<i>♪ You know these reckless thoughts
Of mine are following you ♪</i>

1688
01:32:38,875 --> 01:32:39,875
["Stumblin' In" ends]

1689
01:32:39,958 --> 01:32:42,250
["X's" by Cigarettes After Sex
playing softly]

1690
01:32:53,667 --> 01:32:54,667
So…

1691
01:32:56,875 --> 01:32:57,875
[Poppy] So…

1692
01:32:59,250 --> 01:33:01,208
[exhales] What's next?

1693
01:33:02,458 --> 01:33:03,625
After this?

1694
01:33:04,792 --> 01:33:06,083
[Poppy] Hm…

1695
01:33:07,042 --> 01:33:08,208
I think

1696
01:33:09,167 --> 01:33:11,375
some sweet…

1697
01:33:12,375 --> 01:33:16,042
Air-conditioned lovemaking.

1698
01:33:16,125 --> 01:33:17,292
[Alex] Mm.

1699
01:33:17,375 --> 01:33:18,250
Yeah.

1700
01:33:18,333 --> 01:33:19,208
[Poppy] Mm-hm.

1701
01:33:19,292 --> 01:33:20,958
But after that?

1702
01:33:21,042 --> 01:33:22,458
- [Poppy giggles]
- [Alex chuckles]

1703
01:33:23,250 --> 01:33:25,417
Could you see a life in Linfield?

1704
01:33:25,500 --> 01:33:27,417
- [Poppy laughs]
- Or in New York?

1705
01:33:27,500 --> 01:33:29,583
- [Poppy] Uh… Um…
- What?

1706
01:33:30,333 --> 01:33:32,708
Do we have to talk about this right now?

1707
01:33:32,792 --> 01:33:37,000
I mean, you are jumping on a flight in,
what, like six hours, so…

1708
01:33:37,083 --> 01:33:42,000
Yeah, but… [clears throat]
…I'll call you when I get to New York.

1709
01:33:42,083 --> 01:33:43,083
I know.

1710
01:33:44,000 --> 01:33:46,917
But we're both here right now, so…

1711
01:33:47,917 --> 01:33:49,917
We could just
get on the same page about timelines.

1712
01:33:49,958 --> 01:33:51,958
[Poppy] Shh…

1713
01:33:53,000 --> 01:33:56,167
Don't ruin this moment with an itinerary.

1714
01:34:00,917 --> 01:34:02,208
Hey, I'm kidding.

1715
01:34:03,583 --> 01:34:05,750
N... I just... Let's just…

1716
01:34:06,667 --> 01:34:08,042
Enjoy tonight.

1717
01:34:10,250 --> 01:34:13,708
Talk about all the real-life stuff later.

1718
01:34:13,792 --> 01:34:16,500
This is real life.

1719
01:34:18,917 --> 01:34:21,208
Unless this is just
another vacation for you.

1720
01:34:21,292 --> 01:34:23,208
No, no. Wait, okay.

1721
01:34:24,083 --> 01:34:25,417
Alex, just…

1722
01:34:27,542 --> 01:34:29,625
Give me a minute, you know?

1723
01:34:31,667 --> 01:34:33,042
This just happened.

1724
01:34:33,958 --> 01:34:37,375
Well, I'm sorry
if I need a little time to just…

1725
01:34:39,083 --> 01:34:41,167
Just think things through.

1726
01:34:42,958 --> 01:34:46,083
How is it possible
you still don't know what you want?

1727
01:34:47,417 --> 01:34:48,667
[Poppy scoffs]

1728
01:34:48,750 --> 01:34:50,250
You will always run away.

1729
01:34:52,333 --> 01:34:55,333
Yeah, well, it's better
than being stuck in Linfield waiting.

1730
01:34:55,417 --> 01:34:56,417
For what?

1731
01:34:57,417 --> 01:34:59,542
No, I don't know. What?

1732
01:35:04,208 --> 01:35:05,958
I was waiting for you.

1733
01:35:11,125 --> 01:35:12,125
[Alex sighs]

1734
01:35:16,500 --> 01:35:17,917
This isn't gonna work.

1735
01:35:19,042 --> 01:35:22,208
Not now, not in another ten years.

1736
01:35:22,708 --> 01:35:24,542
Not as long as you're you and I'm me.

1737
01:35:24,625 --> 01:35:26,208
- It's…
- Wait, Alex.

1738
01:35:28,917 --> 01:35:29,917
I love you.

1739
01:35:31,792 --> 01:35:33,250
[whispers] I love you too.

1740
01:35:37,833 --> 01:35:38,833
But, uh

1741
01:35:42,917 --> 01:35:44,833
love has never been our problem.

1742
01:35:50,833 --> 01:35:52,833
[music crescendoes]

1743
01:36:12,167 --> 01:36:13,167
[music fades out]

1744
01:36:22,500 --> 01:36:23,667
[Sarah] Poppy Wright?

1745
01:36:26,875 --> 01:36:28,000
Oh my God.

1746
01:36:28,083 --> 01:36:29,792
- Sarah. Hi.
- [Sarah] Hey.

1747
01:36:31,125 --> 01:36:32,458
Wow, when did this happen?

1748
01:36:33,042 --> 01:36:34,417
Uh, about a year ago. [Chuckles]

1749
01:36:37,208 --> 01:36:40,292
Listen, I'd love to stay and catch up,
but I'm late for my pre-flight.

1750
01:36:40,375 --> 01:36:42,095
- But it was great to see you.
- [Poppy] Yeah.

1751
01:36:43,500 --> 01:36:44,917
Hey, wait, Sarah.

1752
01:36:51,125 --> 01:36:53,583
I was really careless with everything.

1753
01:36:56,125 --> 01:36:57,750
My friendship with Alex…

1754
01:36:58,875 --> 01:37:00,417
Wasn't fair to you.

1755
01:37:02,542 --> 01:37:03,542
I'm sorry.

1756
01:37:07,500 --> 01:37:10,583
You know, I spent a long time
blaming you for our problems.

1757
01:37:11,417 --> 01:37:14,625
I thought that if you just went away,
they'd all get solved. [Chuckles]

1758
01:37:15,125 --> 01:37:19,792
And then you did, and somehow
that was even worse for my relationship.

1759
01:37:21,750 --> 01:37:25,375
But, honestly, you did me a favor.

1760
01:37:26,500 --> 01:37:28,583
I thought I knew what I wanted from life.

1761
01:37:29,875 --> 01:37:31,125
Turns out, I had no idea.

1762
01:37:34,750 --> 01:37:36,125
Bye, Poppy.

1763
01:37:59,708 --> 01:38:00,708
[sad music plays]

1764
01:38:03,833 --> 01:38:05,833
[sad music continues]

1765
01:38:21,292 --> 01:38:23,292
[sad music continues]

1766
01:38:48,583 --> 01:38:50,125
[quietly] This isn't working…

1767
01:38:51,917 --> 01:38:52,917
Is it?

1768
01:38:55,167 --> 01:38:57,167
[pleasant guitar music plays]

1769
01:39:11,542 --> 01:39:13,083
[Swapna] <i>"I need to stop."</i>

1770
01:39:13,583 --> 01:39:16,083
<i>"I need to stay in one place for a while."</i>

1771
01:39:16,167 --> 01:39:19,083
"Most people need
a vacation from their life."

1772
01:39:19,750 --> 01:39:21,250
"And that was never my problem."

1773
01:39:22,292 --> 01:39:24,125
"I need the life part."

1774
01:39:24,208 --> 01:39:26,208
[pleasant music continues]

1775
01:39:27,917 --> 01:39:28,917
[sighs deeply]

1776
01:39:30,958 --> 01:39:34,500
This is the best thing
you've written all year.

1777
01:39:35,500 --> 01:39:38,667
I can't believe
this is a resignation letter.

1778
01:39:39,500 --> 01:39:40,750
I'm sorry.

1779
01:39:40,833 --> 01:39:43,250
Oh, it's fine. [Sighs] Don't worry.

1780
01:39:43,333 --> 01:39:45,125
I'm not gonna beg you to stay.

1781
01:39:45,208 --> 01:39:47,250
Too many people want this job.
It wouldn't be fair.

1782
01:39:47,333 --> 01:39:50,333
And also, obviously, I don't want you here
if you don't want to be here.

1783
01:39:50,917 --> 01:39:52,125
I know.

1784
01:39:52,208 --> 01:39:55,583
I'm not saying this as your boss.
I'm saying this as your…

1785
01:39:56,875 --> 01:39:57,875
Fan.

1786
01:39:59,750 --> 01:40:01,417
Please keep writing.

1787
01:40:02,375 --> 01:40:05,000
Even if it's not here.
Especially if it's not here.

1788
01:40:05,083 --> 01:40:07,875
I think this could be something.

1789
01:40:08,375 --> 01:40:11,917
Like, where does the girl
who's gone everywhere go now?

1790
01:40:20,250 --> 01:40:23,667
If you could be anywhere in the world
right now, where would you go?

1791
01:40:24,542 --> 01:40:26,542
[pleasant music continues]

1792
01:40:28,042 --> 01:40:31,333
[inhales] Have you ever been
to Linfield, Ohio?

1793
01:40:31,833 --> 01:40:32,833
[Swapna] God, no.

1794
01:40:33,292 --> 01:40:34,917
Why? Am I missing something? [Laughs]

1795
01:40:37,583 --> 01:40:38,875
Not really.

1796
01:40:42,958 --> 01:40:44,417
But I think I am.

1797
01:40:45,542 --> 01:40:47,542
[pleasant music continues]

1798
01:40:52,125 --> 01:40:54,125
[pleasant music continues]

1799
01:41:23,417 --> 01:41:25,417
[pleasant music fades out]

1800
01:41:35,542 --> 01:41:37,542
- [rings doorbell]
- [hopeful music plays]

1801
01:41:57,708 --> 01:41:58,708
[Poppy keeps knocking]

1802
01:42:24,542 --> 01:42:25,625
[Poppy] Alex?

1803
01:42:26,208 --> 01:42:27,500
Wait, Alex!

1804
01:42:27,583 --> 01:42:29,833
Alex! Wait, hey!

1805
01:42:30,333 --> 01:42:32,250
Alex!

1806
01:42:32,792 --> 01:42:33,792
[pants]

1807
01:42:35,875 --> 01:42:38,208
Oh, I hate running.

1808
01:42:42,000 --> 01:42:43,500
Alex!

1809
01:42:49,333 --> 01:42:50,750
Alex!

1810
01:42:55,292 --> 01:42:57,292
[panting]

1811
01:43:03,792 --> 01:43:06,083
[moaning, panting]

1812
01:43:08,542 --> 01:43:11,333
[panting]

1813
01:43:18,625 --> 01:43:20,833
[panting slows]

1814
01:43:22,042 --> 01:43:24,042
[hopeful music turns triumphant]

1815
01:43:26,708 --> 01:43:27,958
[Poppy pants harder]

1816
01:43:29,500 --> 01:43:31,250
Alex!

1817
01:43:36,583 --> 01:43:37,583
Alex!

1818
01:43:38,792 --> 01:43:41,042
Alex! No, Alex!

1819
01:43:41,542 --> 01:43:43,250
Alex!

1820
01:43:43,833 --> 01:43:44,667
Oh my God.

1821
01:43:44,750 --> 01:43:46,333
[Poppy's panting slows]

1822
01:43:46,417 --> 01:43:47,792
- Poppy?
- I… Just a second.

1823
01:43:47,875 --> 01:43:49,417
[Poppy catches breath]

1824
01:43:49,500 --> 01:43:50,625
What are you doing here?

1825
01:43:50,708 --> 01:43:52,708
[Poppy breathes deeply]

1826
01:43:56,208 --> 01:43:58,208
[car honks repeatedly]

1827
01:43:58,917 --> 01:44:00,458
Can you tell me over here?

1828
01:44:04,833 --> 01:44:06,833
[pleasant music plays]

1829
01:44:08,500 --> 01:44:10,500
[breathes slowly]

1830
01:44:16,583 --> 01:44:18,042
I always felt like…

1831
01:44:20,583 --> 01:44:23,083
If I stayed in one place too long…

1832
01:44:25,042 --> 01:44:27,625
Everyone would see that I'm too much.

1833
01:44:30,125 --> 01:44:31,250
Even you.

1834
01:44:32,083 --> 01:44:34,542
So one week a year with you…

1835
01:44:36,458 --> 01:44:37,833
It was safe.

1836
01:44:38,792 --> 01:44:40,875
It's all that I thought that I could have.

1837
01:44:43,750 --> 01:44:44,750
But I love you.

1838
01:44:47,542 --> 01:44:49,833
I'm always gonna love you.

1839
01:44:51,875 --> 01:44:55,583
So there's not one thing in my whole life

1840
01:44:56,167 --> 01:44:57,583
that I wouldn't give up…

1841
01:44:59,375 --> 01:45:01,292
To build something new with you.

1842
01:45:03,625 --> 01:45:04,667
Because…

1843
01:45:06,042 --> 01:45:08,875
When I'm sad or sick…

1844
01:45:10,792 --> 01:45:12,125
You're all I want.

1845
01:45:14,750 --> 01:45:18,250
And when I'm happy,
you make me so much happier.

1846
01:45:19,625 --> 01:45:22,000
And I know I have
a lot of things I gotta figure out,

1847
01:45:22,083 --> 01:45:24,042
but if there's one thing that I know,

1848
01:45:25,375 --> 01:45:27,417
it's that wherever you are in the world,

1849
01:45:28,083 --> 01:45:29,417
that's where I belong.

1850
01:45:32,208 --> 01:45:35,500
You're not a vacation to me, Alex.
You're home.

1851
01:45:36,792 --> 01:45:39,042
And I think that I'm that for you too.

1852
01:45:39,125 --> 01:45:41,125
[pleasant music fades out]

1853
01:45:45,542 --> 01:45:46,542
You can…

1854
01:45:48,583 --> 01:45:49,917
You can talk now.

1855
01:45:50,000 --> 01:45:52,125
[hopeful music plays]

1856
01:45:55,458 --> 01:45:57,000
[whispers] Please talk now.

1857
01:45:57,625 --> 01:45:59,625
[triumphant music plays]

1858
01:46:30,458 --> 01:46:32,000
So what do we do now?

1859
01:46:34,583 --> 01:46:37,042
As long as I'm with you, I don't care.

1860
01:46:53,542 --> 01:46:55,542
[triumphant music fades out]

1861
01:46:55,625 --> 01:46:57,625
[serene music plays]

1862
01:47:05,167 --> 01:47:06,750
[Poppy] <i>When people think of home,</i>

1863
01:47:06,833 --> 01:47:09,208
<i>they think of the place where they live,</i>

1864
01:47:09,292 --> 01:47:11,000
<i>or maybe the place they grew up.</i>

1865
01:47:11,083 --> 01:47:13,667
Uh, Kenny G, no. Be nice to your brother.

1866
01:47:13,750 --> 01:47:14,750
[whimpers]

1867
01:47:15,958 --> 01:47:18,708
<i>Those places never felt like home to me.</i>

1868
01:47:20,292 --> 01:47:21,292
Wait.

1869
01:47:21,958 --> 01:47:24,375
Do you teach at Sarah Lawrence?

1870
01:47:24,458 --> 01:47:26,750
Come on. You got me this.
You can't make fun of me.

1871
01:47:26,833 --> 01:47:28,333
I love the school spirit.

1872
01:47:28,417 --> 01:47:32,542
What's the mascot again?
Is it the fighting… Sarah Lawrences?

1873
01:47:32,625 --> 01:47:34,125
- It is the Griffins.
- [Poppy] Hm.

1874
01:47:34,208 --> 01:47:36,417
- Now can you get me the butter, please?
- [Poppy giggles]

1875
01:47:38,583 --> 01:47:42,000
[Poppy] <i>I spent most of my life</i>
<i>looking for somewhere I belonged.</i>

1876
01:47:43,917 --> 01:47:46,917
<i>And believe me, I searched everywhere.</i>

1877
01:47:49,292 --> 01:47:53,375
<i>But it's a thin line
between searching and running away.</i>

1878
01:47:54,792 --> 01:47:56,250
[gasps] Hey, beau.

1879
01:47:56,333 --> 01:47:59,833
<i>So after all my searching,
this is what I've learned.</i>

1880
01:47:59,917 --> 01:48:01,042
Hi, Kenny G.

1881
01:48:01,125 --> 01:48:04,458
[Poppy] <i>Home is where</i>
<i>you can be entirely yourself.</i>

1882
01:48:04,542 --> 01:48:05,875
[serene music continues]

1883
01:48:05,958 --> 01:48:08,750
<i>In fact, home doesn't have
to be a place at all.</i>

1884
01:48:10,333 --> 01:48:13,417
<i>It doesn't matter where you go
or what you do.</i>

1885
01:48:15,792 --> 01:48:20,708
<i>When you're with the person
who loves you for you…</i>

1886
01:48:22,667 --> 01:48:24,167
<i>You're always home.</i>

1887
01:48:25,375 --> 01:48:27,875
<i>Even on vacation.</i>

